</bibRefCitation>
), and a chrysomelid (
<bibRefCitation author="Kingsolver, J. M. &amp; Gibb, T. J. &amp; Pfaffenberger, G. S." box="[736,993,1915,1941]" pageId="24" pageNumber="453" pagination="57 - 82" refId="ref31893" refString="Kingsolver, J. M., Gibb, T. J. &amp; Pfaffenberger, G. S. (1989) Synopsis of the bruchid genus Althaeus Bridwell (Coleoptera) with descriptions of two new species. Transactions of the American Entomological Society, 115, 57 - 82." type="journal article" year="1989">
Kingsolver 
<emphasis box="[870,919,1915,1941]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="453">et al</emphasis>
. 1989
</bibRefCitation>
); a braconid wasp (
<bibRefCitation author="Boring, C. A. &amp; Sharanowski, B. A. J. &amp; Sharkey, M. J." box="[1212,1424,1915,1941]" pageId="24" pageNumber="453" pagination="529 - 548" refId="ref30542" refString="Boring, C. A., Sharanowski, B. A. J. &amp; Sharkey, M. J. (2011) Maxfischeriinae: a new braconid subfamily (Hymenoptera) with highly specialized egg morphology. Systematic Entomology, 36, 529 - 548. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1365 - 3113.2011.00579. x" type="journal article" year="2011">
Boring 
<emphasis box="[1299,1349,1915,1941]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="453">et al</emphasis>
. 2011
</bibRefCitation>
); a sarcophagid fly (
<bibRefCitation author="Dahlem, G. A. &amp; Naczi, R. F. C." box="[360,620,1951,1978]" pageId="24" pageNumber="453" pagination="218 - 240" refId="ref31077" refString="Dahlem, G. A. &amp; Naczi, R. F. C. (2006) Flesh flies (Diptera: Sarcophagidae) associated with North American pitcher plants (Sarraceniaceae), with descriptions of three new species. Annals of the Entomological Society of America, 99, 218 - 240. https: // doi. org / 10.1603 / 0013 - 8746 (2006) 099 [0218: FFDSAW] 2.0. CO; 2" type="journal article" year="2006">Dahlem &amp; Naczi 2006</bibRefCitation>
); and a mouse tapeworm (
<bibRefCitation author="Makarikov, A. A. &amp; Nims, T. N. &amp; Galbreath, K. E. &amp; Hoberg, E. P." box="[913,1168,1950,1977]" pageId="24" pageNumber="453" pagination="2107 - 2117" refId="ref32267" refString="Makarikov, A. A., Nims, T. N., Galbreath, K. E. &amp; Hoberg, E. P. (2015) Hymenolepis folkertsi n. sp. (Eucestoda: Hymenolepididae) in the oldfield mouse Peromyscus polionotus (Wagner) (Rodentia: Cricetidae: Neotominae) from the southeastern Nearctic with comments on tapeworm faunal diversity among deer mice. Parasitology Research, 114, 2107 - 2117. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / s 00436 - 015 - 4399 - x" type="journal article" year="2015">
