<subSubSection pageId="26" pageNumber="455" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="26.[151,1437,150,357]" pageId="26" pageNumber="455">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,332,222,248]" pageId="26" pageNumber="455">Discussion.</emphasis>
This new species is similar to other species in the 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Coquillett" baseAuthorityYear="1901" box="[887,1015,222,249]" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Bezzia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="455" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pulverea">
<emphasis box="[887,904,223,248]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="455">B</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[918,1015,222,248]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="455">pulverea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
complex, but the male genitalia differ from other species in this complex in having narrower parameres, but, as with other species, the aedeagus is also broad with an elongate slender apical section. Finally, the moderately elongate gonostylus lacks well developed apical inner and outer prongs which are also absent in some males of 
<taxonomicName authority="Grogan, 2020" authorityName="Grogan" authorityYear="2020" box="[895,1047,330,357]" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Bezzia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="455" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amblystyla" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[895,912,331,356]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="455">B</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[926,1047,330,356]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="455">amblystyla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1062,1122,331,357]" pageId="26" pageNumber="455" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
